            <scopecontent id="aspace_b8a8d8414a96ab9ded14e7ea39682680">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Typed letters from Anna Murray Vail, at the Paris Depot, to Murray Ledyard, in either Washington, D.C. or Cazenovia, New York. Ledyard was a relative or close friend, since she was addressed as "Dear Murray," and signed with "affection." Vail's letters thank Ledyard for her donations and describe the war and her work in Paris. She discusses the entrance of the U.S. into the war and relations of the A.F.F.W. with the American Red Cross. With the letters is a postcard created for the American Fund for French Wounded showing a woman marking red crosses on supplies and a soldier receiving them. There is also a circular letter dated March 21, 1917. See Folder 6.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
