            <scopecontent id="aspace_a03ce56c01726e95b5804eb1f7f08441">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The circular letters were written and signed by members of the Paris staff.  They were chatty  personal accounts of visits to hospitals,  describing the conditions on the journey, the staff and patients of the hospital, and the distribution of supplies to soldiers. With these are edited extracts of French letters of gratitude from those assisted by the AFFW. The 1915 folder contains one circular letter dated December 21, 1915 and several pages of extracts.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
