            <scopecontent id="aspace_c07dec718b72645c78fddfdd293cab65">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Folder contains printed materials distributed in the U.S. by the War Relief Clearing House for France and her Allies.  This was an American relief organization founded in 1914 and run by prominent men. It collected supplies and funds in New York for distribution in France. The documents discuss the changing relation of this organization with the American Red Cross. The relation the War Relief Clearing House and the AFFW is not clear.</p>
